    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-02T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-02T12:00:00-05:00" n="709"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d709">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.24/5–246: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-02T19:00:00+02:00"
                            >May 2, 1946—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 3—2:51 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>499. Embassy’s telegram 489, May 1.<note n="30" xml:id="d709fn30">Not
                        printed.</note> I presented proposed Lend-Lease settlement<note n="31"
                        xml:id="d709fn31">Since March 29, the Department had been in communication
                        with the Embassy in Turkey on this subject; details not printed.</note> to
                    Foreign Minister this morning. We went over question in some detail. Saka said
                    he fully shared desire reach settlement soon as possible and hoped to set an
                    example so far as Turkey <pb facs="0917" n="905" xml:id="pg_905"/> is concerned.
                    He said proposal would be studied immediately by government experts.</p>
                <p>I expect see Prime Minister<note n="32" xml:id="d709fn32">Sükrü Saraçoğlu.</note>
                    and Minister Finance shortly regarding this matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
